{"id": 232029278, "title": "PM Modi&#039;s pick for 3rd swearing-in ceremony: White kurta-churidar with blue jacket", "text": "Prime Minister Narendra Modi chose a white kurta and churidar with a blue chequered jacket as he took oath for the third consecutive time on Sunday, June 9. The politician paired his dress with black shoes for the swearing-in ceremony at the forecourts of the Rashtrapati Bhavan.When he took the oath as the prime minister for the first time in 2014, Modi had worn a cream linen kurta-pyjama with a beige golden jacket. For his 2019 swearing-in ceremony, the prime minister chose a similar dress paired with a beige jacket.Who gets which ministry in Modi 3.0? Form your 'Dream Cabinet' and win prizes.link__elec{padding:0 0 12px} .link__elec div{margin-bottom:7px;}.link__elec a{color: var(--linkcolor); text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px; line-height:24px; font-weight:600;} Kurtas and bandhgala jackets are Modi's popular choice on important occasions. He is also known for sporting flamboyant and colourful turbans during Independence Day and Republic Day celebrations. PM Modi chose a multi-coloured \"bandhani\" print safa for his Republic Day look in January this year.He is the second PM after Jawaharlal Nehru to be elected for a third consecutive term.Along with Modi, senior BJP leaders Rajnath Singh, Nitin Gadkari and Amit Shah also took oath as cabinet ministers, while party president JP Nadda returned to the cabinet after five years, indicating the Prime Minister's focus on continuity and experience in his third term.Published By: Trisha BhattacharyaPublished On: Jun 9, 2024ALSO READ | PM Modi takes oath for record 3rd term, 72 ministers with himMust Watch", "summary": "<a href=\"https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/pm-modis-pick-for-3rd-swearing-in-ceremony-white-kurta-churidar-with-blue-jacket-2551054-2024-06-09\"> <img align=\"left\" hspace=\"2\" height=\"180\" width=\"305\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"https://akm-img-a-in.tosshub.com/i